// 1. Encapsulation :
// Class Or Struct
// Seperate The Data(Attributes) Definition From Its Use
/I Setter Getter Method - Properties|
// Employee
// Id Name salary
// 1. End User Access data itself
// 2. No Data Validation
// 3. No Read Only Filed

// How to Apply Encapsulation:
// 1. Make All Data(Attributes) Private
// 2. Access Data Through :
// 2.1. Setter Getter Method
// 2.2. Properties

// Apply Encapsulation Using Properties:
// 1. Full Property
// 2. Automatic Property
// 3. Special Property [Indexer]

Car C01;
// Decalre For Refernce (Pointer) From Type 'Car'
// C01 : Can Refer To Object From Type 'Car' Or Any Class Inherited 
// C01 : Refer To Null
//Console WriteLine(C01);
// 8 Bytes Will Be Allocated At STACK For The Reference 'C01'
// o Bytes Will Be Allocated At HEAP


C01 = new Car();
// new
// 1. Allocate The Number Of Required Bytes At HEAP For The 0bject
// 2. Initailized The Allocated Bytes With The Default Value
// 3. Call User-Defined Constructor if Exists
// 4. Assign The Object To The Reference
